<dl id="n35248b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35248b">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35248b"> 248(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 30 Tyrants</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Plutarch&apos;s statement that the <mark>Thirty</mark> Tyrants removed the bema <font color="green">[the large rock on the Pnyx on which the orators stood, which primitively had been an altar of Zeus]</font> so as to face the land instead of the sea is probably due to a misunderstanding. <small> &ldquo;ATHENS&rdquo; <a name="EBAT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBAT"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 833c</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
